author: sussman
msg: Adding keyword logic to existing EOL logic for checkouts/updates.
NOTE: this commit will temporarily break the build, until CMike
commits his 'keyword structure' change.  We're about to do a conflict
resolution in front of his screen.
* wc.h (SVN_WC__LOG_ATTR_EXPAND): new logfile attribute.
* get_editor.c (close_file): and keyword logic to EOL logic, even
though it will need to be update a bit when cmpilato commits his
'keyword structure' change.  Also, write out 'svn:entry:' props at
the beginning of the function (not the end), so that if the textual
merging process needs to expand keywords, the values will be
up-to-date.

author: gstein
msg: Fix some problems in the wcprop fetching code.
* libsvn_wc/props.c (wcprop_list): the prop fetching code should not care
whether the working copy file truly exists or not. or, at a minimum,
should just state that "no properties" exist if the WC file isn't
there.
[some design/intent input needed here]
(svn_wc__wcprop_get): watch out for undefined properties. set the output
to NULL for these.
